name: ASUS BIOS File
summary: Learn about .CMO files and view a list of programs that open them.

content: CMO files are only used on Windows-based computers and not on Mac computers. They are typically saved on a USB device, which can be loaded on to a computer. To load a CMO file on a computer, follow these instructions:
Insert the USB storage device storing the CMO file
Choose the drive with the BIOS profile you want and click "Enter"
NOTE: BIOS stands for "Basic Input/Output System" and is a type of firmware used by a computer's microprocessor to boot the computer system when it is turned on.
